{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-04219/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-04219"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:42:19"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, handheld, pan, tracking"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["three shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A woman and mile smile at each other."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04219/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-04219","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04219/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-04219"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04219/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04219/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04219/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04219/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04219/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04219/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04219/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04219/canvas/1/badb7681-7eaf-4dfc-ad63-e43b2f14cf46","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T19:18:08.795Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>In contrast to <em>There Will Be Blood</em>, in which Daniel Day-Lewis's Daniel Plainview is focused exclusively on “finding oil,” according to PTA, <em>Phantom Thread </em>offered the actor an opportunity to expand his character’s motivations and, therefore, his own involvement in the production: “This time everything was about personal taste and choice and the theatre that this character is creating in his workplace, right? So, thank God for Daniel picking the drapes, picking the wardrobe, everything. He worked so closely with Mark Tinsley, our production designer, Mark Bridges, the costume designer, to meticulously comb through every last detail. It's why the film looks so good...I honestly don't have the patience that they all had...I would kind of be involved, pretend that I was not glazing over. At a certain point, I was like, ‘Just tell me when you pick the fabric’” (Xixax TV, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW159499794 BCX4\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rdEDLwX49cY\"><u>PHANTOM THREAD - AUDIO - Paul Thomas Anderson interviewed on the Empire podcast</u></a>”).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04219/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:360.4845222072678,97.46971736204586,568.5060565275909,478.0619111709287"}}}]}]}]}